-- Chelsea Wants to Sign Torres After Latest Injury Setback: Soccer Roundup
-- Peter Evans
-- 2010-07-15T09:50:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/chelsea-wants-to-sign-torres-after-latest-injury-setback-soccer-roundup.html

          
          
             The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  
 Torres Targeted  
 Chelsea wants to sign Liverpool’s  Fernando Torres 
after sensing his latest injury setback could persuade the
striker to leave Anfield, the  Daily Mail  reported.  
 The Blues have promised to use the Spaniard “sparingly”
and would put less pressure on the World Cup winner to recover
from injury, according to the Mail.  
 Bellamy Out?  
 Manchester City has decided it can sell  Craig Bellamy  after
the signing of 25 million-pound ($38.3 million)  David Silva  to
replace him, the  Guardian  said.  
 Bellamy must decide whether to stay and battle former
Valencia player Silva for his place, or seek a new club, the
newspaper said.  
 Lahm Move  
 Manchester United wants to sign Bayern Munich right-back
 Philipp Lahm , the  Daily Mail  said.  
 In return, Bayern has expressed interest in United
midfielder  Ji-sung Park  and the German club could ask for a
cash-plus-player deal for Lahm, according to the report.  
 Sven Snub  
 Ivory Coast manager Sven-Goran Eriksson is likely to reject
an offer to become Fulham’s new manager, the  Daily Mirror 
reported.  
 The former England boss is considering staying on as the
West African country’s national coach until the next World Cup.  
